","target":"Author/Dejan Stojković","line":93},{"title":"Author/Anabela Martins","target":"Author/Anabela Martins","line":94},{"title":"Author/Anabela Martins","target":"Author/Anabela Martins","line":95},{"title":"Author/Anabela Martins","target":"Author/Anabela Martins","line":96},{"title":"Author/Marina Sokóvić","target":"Author/Marina Sokóvić","line":97},{"title":"Author/Marina Soković","target":"Author/Marina Soković","line":98},{"title":"Author/Isabel C. F. R. Ferreira","target":"Author/Isabel C. F. R. Ferreira","line":99},{"title":"Author/Isabel C. F. R. Ferreira","target":"Author/Isabel C. F. R. Ferreira","line":100},{"title":"PDF","target":"biblib/vieira_wild_2016/vieira_wild_2016.pdf","line":102}],"metadata":{"id":"vieira_wild_2016","type":"article-journal","title":"Wild Morchella conica Pers. from different origins: a comparative study of nutritional and bioactive properties","issued":{"date-parts":[[2016]]},"DOI":"10.1002/jsfa.7063","container-title":"Journal of the Science of Food and Agriculture","abstract":"BACKGROUND Morchella conica Pers. is a species of fungus that belongs to the Morchellaceae family and was studied in order to obtain more information about this species, by comparing Portuguese and Serbian wild samples. Free sugars, fatty acids, tocopherols, organic and phenolic acids were analysed by chromatographic techniques. M. conica methanolic extracts were tested regarding antioxidant and antimicrobial properties. The absence of hepatotoxicity was confirmed in porcine liver primary cells. RESULTS The nutrition value varied between the two samples and the Serbian one gave the highest energy contribution and content in sugars, polyunsaturated fatty acids and phenolic compounds, while the Portuguese sample was richer in saturated and monounsaturated fatty acids, tocopherols and organic acids. In general, the Portuguese sample revealed the highest antioxidant potential (except for lipid peroxidation inhibition), while the Serbian one displayed higher antimicrobial activity. None of the samples revealed toxicity towards liver cells. CONCLUSION The present study provides new data concerning chemical characterization and bioactivity of Morchella conica Pers. © 2014 Society of Chemical Industry","tags":["#literature_note"],"author":[{"family":"Vieira","given":"Vanessa","literal":""},{"family":"Vieira","given":"Vanessa","literal":""},{"family":"Vieira","given":"Vanessa Pedrosa","literal":""},{"family":"Fernandes","given":"Ângela","literal":""},{"family":"Fernandes","given":"Ângela","literal":""},{"family":"Barros","given":"Lillian","literal":""},{"family":"Barros","given":"Lillian","literal":""},{"family":"Glamočlija","given":"Jasmina","literal":""},{"family":"Glamočlija","given":"Jasmina","literal":""},{"family":"Ćirić","given":"Ana","literal":""},{"family":"Ćirić","given":"Ana","literal":""},{"family":"Stojković","given":"Dejan","literal":""},{"family":"Stojković","given":"Dejan","literal":""},{"family":"Martins","given":"Anabela","literal":""},{"family":"Martins","given":"Anabela","literal":""},{"family":"Martins","given":"Anabela","literal":""},{"family":"Sokóvić","given":"Marina","literal":""},{"family":"Soković","given":"Marina","literal":""},{"family":"Ferreira","given":"Isabel C. F. R.","literal":""},{"family":"Ferreira","given":"Isabel C. F. R.","literal":""}],"citation-key":"vieira_wild_2016","year":"2016","dateCreated":"2026-03-31","reading-status":"to-read","aliases":["Wild Morchella conica Pers. from different origins: a comparative study of nutritional and bioactive properties"],"author-links":["[[Author/Vanessa Vieira]]","[[Author/Vanessa Vieira]]","[[Author/Vanessa Pedrosa Vieira]]","[[Author/Ângela Fernandes]]","[[Author/Ângela Fernandes]]","[[Author/Lillian Barros]]","[[Author/Lillian Barros]]","[[Author/Jasmina Glamočlija]]","[[Author/Jasmina Glamočlija]]","[[Author/Ana Ćirić]]","[[Author/Ana Ćirić]]","[[Author/Dejan Stojković]]","[[Author/Dejan Stojković]]","[[Author/Anabela Martins]]","[[Au